Very nice Japanese food restaurant. We experienced very good service when we arrived. They have an extensive menu and very good sake selections. The sashimi we ordered was fresh and of good quality. We also ordered the deluxe plate sushi, ribeye steak, karaage chicken and Rinka roll. The desert just was ok. This is a pricey restaurant but the food was very good. No issues with parking as there is a free parking structure right across the street.

Exceptional food! Dined here for lunch.. I was blown away, and I’ve dined at hundreds if not thousands of Japanese restaurants so that this compliment is not given lightly. For those haters out there, dine at your Morimoto and fancy sushi places because it is hard for you to comprehend what perfect rice is and why it takes so many years for a sushi apprentice to learn how to prepare sushi rice and Japanese stock properly, and the intricate ways of preparing “basic” dishes. Hawaiians and visitors are lucky to have this restaurant.

I used to love the food at Rinka's original location off of Keeaumoku Street and was excited to see that they'd opened a new location in Kaka'ako next to Whole Foods. I visited Rinka with a small group for a noon lunch and arrived early to ensure we'd get a table. The restaurant was full, but they were able to accommodate us with a table in the private room located in the back of the main dining room. The size and decor of the new location is so much better than the old one which was much smaller and truth be told had a lot of negative energy attached to it. This new space is modern with lots of light and high ceilings.  For our meal we each chose a set from their lunch menu. Each set runs anywhere from $16-$25 depending on what you order, and it's a lot of food! You get your main entree, bowl of rice, pickles, chawanmushi and two small side dishes, which will make your belly very full and happy! For my entree I chose the nabeyaki udon which came with a wonderful pickle and ume rice that I devoured.  If you're looking for a truly authentic Japanese restaurant I think you'll love Rinka! Service is friendly and for now, it's BYOB until they get their liquor license. Other reviewers wrote that they do take reservations but they weren't taking reservations during lunch. There's tons of parking at Whole Foods with an adjacent elevator near Rinka's entrance.
Good place to have a quality Japanese food for lunch.

Highly recommend their lunch specials. There are lot more menu items for dinner, but it can get expensive.  Came here for lunch to try out their lunch specials and I loved it! I enjoyed the Daily Special which was a Negitoro Don (~$18) and an udon. The set also came with chawanmushi and 2 small sides you can choose from. The negitoro was very good and their rice is just excellent!. The sukiyaki was also good. It was a tad sweet for me and I wish there was more meat. It does come with a raw egg to dip the beef in.  The interior is new and very bright. Service was good. They were very helpful in answering questions about the menu.  Parking is in the Whole Foods structure.
